263
00:21:34.173 --> 00:21:36.141
A physician! Quickly!

264
00:21:36.208 --> 00:21:37.903
Give us cover!
Give us cover, now!

265
00:21:41.313 --> 00:21:43.337
Cover him!

266
00:21:43.782 --> 00:21:45.640
Cover the King.

267
00:21:45.651 --> 00:21:47.881
Physician!

268
00:21:48.921 --> 00:21:50.779
Why, Loxley? Are you not feeling well?

269
00:21:50.856 --> 00:21:52.853
Physician!

270
00:21:59.064 --> 00:22:00.956
Wine.

271
00:22:23.255 --> 00:22:25.154
What's this?

272
00:22:25.824 --> 00:22:28.685
The King is dead!
Dead?

273
00:22:28.794 --> 00:22:30.186
Dead.

274
00:22:30.262 --> 00:22:34.926
All right, then, Jimmy. Knock the pegs out.
We make our own fate from now on!

275
00:22:38.470 --> 00:22:39.835
I'll come with you.

276
00:22:39.905 --> 00:22:42.840
No, you're not.
We don't take strays.

277
00:22:42.908 --> 00:22:43.932
The more the merrier.

278
00:22:44.009 --> 00:22:45.943
The road will be dangerous.
He might be useful.

279
00:22:46.011 --> 00:22:47.035
Where we going?

280
00:22:47.112 --> 00:22:50.741
To the coast and to a boat before
3,000 desperate soldiers get there

281
00:22:50.816 --> 00:22:53.516
and the price for a Channel
crossing goes up a hundredfold.

282
00:22:53.585 --> 00:22:54.650
What about our wages?

283
00:22:54.720 --> 00:22:57.780
If you thought it was hard getting
wages while he was alive,

284
00:22:57.856 --> 00:22:59.721
try getting paid by a dead king.

285
00:22:59.792 --> 00:23:02.989
All right, boys, collect your
gear as quick as you can.

286
00:23:03.095 --> 00:23:05.487
<font color="#ff80ff">(CHURCH BELL RINGING)</font>

287
00:23:08.767 --> 00:23:10.632
<font color="#ff80ff">FRIAR TUCK:</font> I like the new church.

288
00:23:13.739 --> 00:23:15.070
Lady Marion.

289
00:23:15.140 --> 00:23:20.742
I would have been sorry to leave
without your farewell. Thank you.

290
00:23:21.513 --> 00:23:23.947
I'm glad to speed you on your
way, Father Tancred,

291
00:23:24.016 --> 00:23:27.383
but it was to seek out
our new shepherd.

292
00:23:27.453 --> 00:23:32.413
You have lately been missed at
Sunday worship and my sermons.

293
00:23:32.725 --> 00:23:36.961
I like a quiet church, Father,
when I pray for a miracle.

294
00:23:43.869 --> 00:23:47.999
Your new flock is women,
children and old folk.

295
00:23:48.073 --> 00:23:50.234
