351
00:30:26.905 --> 00:30:28.236
Do you know it?

352
00:30:28.306 --> 00:30:31.070
Aye, I've heard of Nottingham.

353
00:30:31.443 --> 00:30:33.567
<font color="#ff80ff">(EXHALING)</font>

354
00:30:34.713 --> 00:30:36.180
Then the fate.. .

355
00:30:36.248 --> 00:30:38.375
The fates have smiled on me.

356
00:30:40.552 --> 00:30:41.576
<font color="#ff80ff">(SNORTING)</font>

357
00:30:41.653 --> 00:30:46.147
You must take the
sword to my father.

358
00:30:47.359 --> 00:30:49.659
It will bring me peace.

359
00:30:52.631 --> 00:30:56.226
I took it in anger and
without his consent.

360
00:30:57.669 --> 00:31:00.797
You must understand
the bond of love

361
00:31:00.872 --> 00:31:03.067
between a father and his son.

362
00:31:03.542 --> 00:31:07.535
My father abandoned me to the
world of men when I was 6 years old.

363
00:31:07.612 --> 00:31:10.240
I know little of the love
between father and son.

364
00:31:10.916 --> 00:31:12.647
I beg you.

365
00:31:12.684 --> 00:31:14.345
Longstride,

366
00:31:14.419 --> 00:31:16.286
say you will.

367
00:31:20.926 --> 00:31:22.720
I will.

368
00:31:42.881 --> 00:31:45.008
It's a pact sworn
in blood, Robin.

369
00:31:45.283 --> 00:31:48.878
lt's a scratch, Allan, and that's all it is.

370
00:32:09.174 --> 00:32:11.034
<font color="#ff80ff">WILL:</font> Robin!

371
00:32:17.382 --> 00:32:21.545
Loxley was making for the
coast to meet the ship.

372
00:32:24.556 --> 00:32:26.583
That crown could be
our passage home.

373
00:32:26.625 --> 00:32:28.115
We're common archers, Robin.

374
00:32:28.193 --> 00:32:31.460
If we arrive at the King's ship with
his crown, we'll be accused of murder.

375
00:32:31.463 --> 00:32:33.363
How do you know

376
00:32:33.431 --> 00:32:37.629
that the knights you see walking
about are actually knights at all?

377
00:32:37.702 --> 00:32:40.193
There is no difference
between a knight

378
00:32:40.272 --> 00:32:44.432
and any other man
aside from what he wears.

379
00:32:44.442 --> 00:32:47.010
All we need is about us.

380
00:32:47.112 --> 00:32:50.675
Armor, helmets, swords,

381
00:32:52.217 --> 00:32:56.309
and we make England wealthy men

382
